description: Unless you hired Stevie Wonder, there is NO reason why I should have to meet the building inspector to point out the decrepit state of this house at 22 Marion Street (I was told several months ago that I had to meet the inspector to point out the violations which are CLEARLY VISIBLE from the street.). It's a drug den with small children being brought in and out AND LITERALLY FALLING APART!  I know A-7 has requested that it be condemned, but no response.  Does a small child have to die before someone comes out to look at this?  Does there have to be a fatal fire before the City does it's job?  There is at least one OD at this house per month.  The people living there should get frequent ambulance points for how often someone is brought out of there.  (After 3 rides, the 4th is free!)  I'm sure if Mayor Marty had a house like this on his block, it would get an Extreme Makeover pronto!
